               <p>ROBERT BOYD. I am a <rs id="t18280911-241-viclabel1233" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-241-victim1358 t18280911-241-viclabel1233"></join>. On the 16th of August I was working at an unfinished house in <placeName id="t18280911-241-crimeloc1234">St. Pancras</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-241-crimeloc1234" type="placeName" value="St. Pancras"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-241-crimeloc1234" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-241-off1231 t18280911-241-crimeloc1234"></join> - I left all my tools there at night; there were a saw, planes, trowels, and other things - my son went on the Sunday to see if they were all safe, and they were gone - I saw them again on the 19th.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-241-person1359">
                  WILLIAM 
                  KIRBY
               <interp inst="t18280911-241-person1359" type="surname" value="KIRBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-241-person1359" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-241-person1359" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner on Saffron-hill, on the Sunday, with these tools on his shoulder - he said they were his own, and he had brought them from Hornsey.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. On the Sunday morning I met a young man, who asked me if I knew any body who wanted to purchase these things - he said he would sell them for 10s., and I bought them.</p>
